We're gonna do it North's way.

1037
01:06:49,200 --> 01:06:52,520
If you want to come along,
that'd be fine.

1038
01:06:52,560 --> 01:06:54,480
We could use your help.

1039
01:06:54,560 --> 01:06:57,240
Two of us doubles our chances.

1040
01:06:57,320 --> 01:06:59,880
We better get going.

1041
01:07:00,040 --> 01:07:02,560
It's a straight shot!

1042
01:07:02,640 --> 01:07:04,640
Straight shot.

1043
01:07:07,720 --> 01:07:09,520
Keep this on channel 3.

1044
01:07:09,600 --> 01:07:10,720
Yeah.

1045
01:07:10,800 --> 01:07:12,920
It should work for a while.

1046
01:07:14,480 --> 01:07:15,840
See you tonight.

1047
01:07:22,680 --> 01:07:26,480
Abby, you're in charge.

1048
01:07:26,560 --> 01:07:30,840
Uh, stay strong, everybody.

1049
01:07:34,840 --> 01:07:36,240
We'll be back with help.

1050
01:07:41,200 --> 01:07:42,480
[engine starting]

1051
01:07:47,040 --> 01:07:48,680
Won't leave you guys here.

1052
01:08:26,640 --> 01:08:28,520
You see that?

1053
01:08:28,560 --> 01:08:30,080
What did I tell you?

1054
01:08:42,160 --> 01:08:43,440
Hey!

1055
01:08:43,480 --> 01:08:47,320
Anybody here?

1056
01:08:50,960 --> 01:08:54,240
Supposed to be here. This is...

1057
01:08:54,320 --> 01:08:55,840
This is Tuesday, isn't it?

1058
01:08:55,920 --> 01:08:57,000
All day.

1059
01:09:07,440 --> 01:09:09,240
What is going on?

1060
01:09:09,320 --> 01:09:10,960
God damn it.

1061
01:09:11,040 --> 01:09:12,120
Hey!

1062
01:09:53,360 --> 01:09:54,680
No juice at all.

1063
01:09:56,960 --> 01:10:00,680
Must have got a ride out of here.

1064
01:10:08,160 --> 01:10:10,640
Well?

1065
01:10:10,720 --> 01:10:13,800
There's a pumping station
about 25 miles west of here.

1066
01:10:13,880 --> 01:10:19,240
No, Ed. Fort Crow
is about 8 or 9 miles south of here.

1067
01:10:19,280 --> 01:10:21,960
Ed! Fort Crow is gonna save our ass!

1068
01:10:22,000 --> 01:10:24,920
[pulling starter]

1069
01:10:25,000 --> 01:10:26,680
- Uhh!
- [motor sputters]

1070
01:10:26,760 --> 01:10:28,640
- Uhh!
- [motor sputters]

1071
01:10:32,800 --> 01:10:33,800
Come on! Fucking piece of shit!

1072
01:10:33,880 --> 01:10:35,880
Pollack! Pollack!

1073
01:10:35,920 --> 01:10:37,440
What?

1074
01:10:37,520 --> 01:10:39,120
We lost all our oil.

1075
01:10:39,200 --> 01:10:40,160
She's not gonna start.

1076
01:10:43,240 --> 01:10:44,600
Fuck!

1077
01:10:53,760 --> 01:10:55,600
All right, Ed, listen.

1078
01:10:55,680 --> 01:10:59,600
Fort Crow is 9 miles
south of here, maybe 10.

1079
01:10:59,680 --> 01:11:02,600
We got three hours of daylight left.

1080
01:11:02,640 --> 01:11:04,120
Let's not squander it.

1081
01:11:11,920 --> 01:11:13,400
9 miles.

1082
01:11:15,960 --> 01:11:20,560
<i>Out there on foot.</i>

1083
01:11:22,320 --> 01:11:23,920
God damn it.

1084
01:12:00,400 --> 01:12:02,960
[distant rumbling]

1085
01:12:17,440 --> 01:12:19,080
[Dawn]
He's gone.

1086
01:12:19,120 --> 01:12:20,400
[Abby]
Let's cover him up.

1087
01:12:30,840 --> 01:12:33,080
Where's Lee?

1088
01:13:12,240 --> 01:13:15,920
Pollack! You see that ridge?

1089
01:13:15,960 --> 01:13:18,800
Fort Crow is on the other side.

1090
01:13:27,800 --> 01:13:31,840
River around here somewhere.

1091
01:13:37,360 --> 01:13:38,280
[gasps]

1092
01:13:51,720 --> 01:13:53,160
What are you doing?

1093
01:13:58,160 --> 01:14:01,040
[sobbing]

1094
01:14:11,760 --> 01:14:14,400
Think he was one of those drivers?

1095
01:14:16,720 --> 01:14:18,240
From the ice road?

1096
01:14:32,520 --> 01:14:34,320
Pollack!

1097
01:14:36,760 --> 01:14:38,480
Pollack!

1098
01:14:38,560 --> 01:14:39,640
[ice cracking]

1099
01:14:44,560 --> 01:14:45,600
Hang on!

1100
01:14:54,640 --> 01:14:56,000
Hang on, Pollack!

1101
01:14:56,080 --> 01:14:57,680
[grunt]

1102
01:15:02,640 --> 01:15:03,520
Pollack!

1103
01:15:03,600 --> 01:15:04,640
My foot!

1104
01:15:06,280 --> 01:15:07,360
The belt!

1105
01:15:07,440 --> 01:15:08,560
Can you grab it?

1106
01:15:08,640 --> 01:15:09,600
Aah!

1107
01:15:17,680 --> 01:15:18,600
That's it.

1108
01:15:18,640 --> 01:15:21,960
All right.
Hang on a second!

1109
01:15:31,320 --> 01:15:33,320
Pull! Pull!

1110
01:15:33,400 --> 01:15:34,720
Fuck!

1111
01:15:39,080 --> 01:15:41,120
Get it!
[grunt]

1112
01:15:42,440 --> 01:15:43,480
Uhhn!

1113
01:15:43,560 --> 01:15:45,160
- I can't do it.
- Yes, you can.

1114
01:15:45,240 --> 01:15:46,200
I can't do it.

1115
01:15:46,280 --> 01:15:48,360
Yes, you can. Come on, Pollack.

1116
01:15:49,800 --> 01:15:51,040
Uhh!

1117
01:15:52,600 --> 01:15:55,040
We gotta get off this ice.
It's not stable.

1118
01:15:58,640 --> 01:16:00,560
Come on. Come on.

1119
01:16:04,880 --> 01:16:06,360
Come on!

1120
01:16:20,080 --> 01:16:22,800
All right. You're doing great!

1121
01:16:22,840 --> 01:16:23,840
You're doing great.

1122
01:16:23,920 --> 01:16:26,040
Come on, we gotta get this off.

1123
01:16:26,120 --> 01:16:27,720
- Shit!
- Ah, fuck, man!

1124
01:16:27,760 --> 01:16:28,840
My boot.

1125
01:16:28,880 --> 01:16:30,040
- Forget about the boot.
- I gotta go get my boot.

1126
01:16:30,120 --> 01:16:32,520
No! Forget about the boot, Pollack!
The boot's gone.

1127
01:16:32,560 --> 01:16:33,800
Boot's gone.

1128
01:16:33,840 --> 01:16:36,080
We gotta get those clothes off you.

1129
01:16:36,120 --> 01:16:38,120
Thanks, man.

1130
01:16:38,200 --> 01:16:39,120
Fucking...

1131
01:16:39,160 --> 01:16:40,080
I'm fucking burning up.

1132
01:16:40,120 --> 01:16:42,000
No, you're not, you're freezing.

1133
01:16:42,040 --> 01:16:44,480
Keep moving, keep moving!

1134
01:16:44,560 --> 01:16:46,120
You're gonna make it.

1135
01:16:46,160 --> 01:16:47,720
Let's go. Here we go.

1136
01:16:47,760 --> 01:16:48,960
<i>Okay.</i>

1137
01:17:11,760 --> 01:17:12,720
Come on.

1138
01:17:18,440 --> 01:17:19,720
Atta boy.

1139
01:17:50,320 --> 01:17:52,480
Take it easy with that stuff.

1140
01:17:52,560 --> 01:17:54,600
It doesn't mix well with hypothermia.

1141
01:18:00,160 --> 01:18:02,600
[Ed]
We could die out here.

1142
01:18:13,160 --> 01:18:14,760
That gonna be a boot?

1143
01:18:14,840 --> 01:18:17,880
Yep.

1144
01:18:22,080 --> 01:18:23,840
Anyway, I, uh...

1145
01:18:26,800 --> 01:18:29,360
Well, anyway...

1146
01:18:29,440 --> 01:18:30,400
You know.

1147
01:18:33,640 --> 01:18:35,000
You and Abby.

1148
01:18:36,880 --> 01:18:39,320
[sigh]

1149
01:18:39,400 --> 01:18:41,000
I guess I get it.

1150
01:18:43,720 --> 01:18:45,120
She's a...

1151
01:18:50,960 --> 01:18:53,720
She means a lot to me.

1152
01:18:53,800 --> 01:18:58,440
I guess we had our go at it.

1153
01:19:06,120 --> 01:19:08,080
She's a handful.

1154
01:19:20,600 --> 01:19:23,640
Believe in God?

1155
01:19:27,840 --> 01:19:29,720
No.

1156
01:19:29,800 --> 01:19:31,880
Not the way you mean.

1157
01:19:36,720 --> 01:19:39,680
Jesus Christ, Jim.

1158
01:19:39,760 --> 01:19:43,960
I would not do what you've
chosen to do up here.

1159
01:19:47,800 --> 01:19:50,600
Whatever god it is that sanctions that,

1160
01:19:50,640 --> 01:19:52,040
then no.

1161
01:19:54,640 --> 01:19:56,400
I'm not a believer.

1162
01:19:58,360 --> 01:20:02,920
What's needed out here is a pipeline

1163
01:20:03,000 --> 01:20:04,960
and a base camp...

1164
01:20:06,880 --> 01:20:08,600
and a couple of wells.

1165
01:20:08,680 --> 01:20:10,400
That's what God wants.

1166
01:20:18,160 --> 01:20:20,040
[Dawn]
Lee!

1167
01:20:34,160 --> 01:20:35,160
[muffled shouting]

1168
01:20:35,240 --> 01:20:36,360
Dawn.

1169
01:20:36,400 --> 01:20:37,320
Dawn?

1170
01:20:37,360 --> 01:20:39,440
[muffled shouting]

1171
01:20:39,520 --> 01:20:41,600
Dawn!

1172
01:20:41,680 --> 01:20:43,080
Dawn?

1173
01:20:43,120 --> 01:20:44,840
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

1174
01:20:44,920 --> 01:20:47,080
<i>Oh, my God! Motor!</i>

1175
01:20:47,160 --> 01:20:49,040
[Abby]
Motor?

1176
01:20:49,080 --> 01:20:50,040
Motor!

1177
01:20:51,280 --> 01:20:52,840
- Motor!
- [Dawn laughing]

1178
01:20:52,920 --> 01:20:54,040
Dawn, what did you do?

1179
01:20:54,120 --> 01:20:55,920
Motor!

1180
01:20:56,000 --> 01:20:57,760
[laughing]

1181
01:20:57,840 --> 01:20:59,320
Motor!

1182
01:21:01,240 --> 01:21:02,760
Dawn!

1183
01:21:02,800 --> 01:21:04,040
Ha ha ha ha!

1184
01:21:04,120 --> 01:21:06,040
What's wrong with you?

1185
01:21:06,120 --> 01:21:07,000
Dawn!

1186
01:21:07,080 --> 01:21:08,240
Aah!

1187
01:21:08,320 --> 01:21:09,120
No!

1188
01:21:09,200 --> 01:21:10,240
[loud banging]

1189
01:21:10,320 --> 01:21:11,240
[metal clanging]

1190
01:21:11,280 --> 01:21:13,200
[thump]

1191
01:21:25,680 --> 01:21:26,760
Motor.

1192
01:21:34,840 --> 01:21:36,720
[sobbing]

1193
01:21:38,600 --> 01:21:39,920
God.

1194
01:21:43,520 --> 01:21:44,560
[banging on door]

1195
01:21:44,640 --> 01:21:47,080
[flipping lock]

1196
01:21:55,080 --> 01:21:57,520
[water dripping]

1197
01:22:04,400 --> 01:22:05,640
[light buzzing]

1198
01:22:09,240 --> 01:22:11,240
[moaning]

1199
01:22:21,600 --> 01:22:24,160
[caw]

1200
01:22:24,240 --> 01:22:26,840
[cawing]

1201
01:22:26,920 --> 01:22:30,160
[banging on wall]

1202
01:22:30,200 --> 01:22:31,840
[wind blowing]

1203
01:22:36,800 --> 01:22:38,480
Dawn!

1204
01:22:42,480 --> 01:22:43,560
Dawn!

1205
01:22:48,400 --> 01:22:50,200
Listen up.

1206
01:22:50,280 --> 01:22:52,000
This is how it's gotta go.

1207
01:22:54,960 --> 01:22:57,200
I want your boots.

1208
01:22:57,280 --> 01:22:58,440
What?

1209
01:22:58,480 --> 01:23:02,040
I'm in charge here,
and that's the decision.

1210
01:23:03,160 --> 01:23:04,880
[distant rumbling]

1211
01:23:10,360 --> 01:23:11,320
What is it?

1212
01:23:17,080 --> 01:23:18,840
Hoffman, what is it?

1213
01:23:18,920 --> 01:23:20,440
I can't tell.

1214
01:23:20,520 --> 01:23:22,120
It's wind!

1215
01:23:23,400 --> 01:23:25,040
Enough of this shit!

1216
01:23:25,120 --> 01:23:28,120
You got into Maxwell's head,
but you're not getting into mine.

1217
01:23:28,200 --> 01:23:30,000
Now I'm not afraid of this place!

1218
01:23:30,080 --> 01:23:32,520
You see it? Do you see it?

1219
01:23:33,840 --> 01:23:35,240
Do you see it?

1220
01:23:37,320 --> 01:23:40,600
Hoffman, you are as crazy
as a shithouse rat.

1221
01:23:40,680 --> 01:23:43,280
Now I'm going for help.
and help is over that rock.

1222
01:23:43,360 --> 01:23:46,080
We gotta stick together.
We can't split up.

1223
01:23:46,160 --> 01:23:48,360
We have no idea what we're dealing with here.

1224
01:23:48,400 --> 01:23:49,840
We gotta watch each others' back.

1225
01:23:49,920 --> 01:23:51,360
You gotta calm down, man!

1226
01:23:54,000 --> 01:23:54,880
Look!

1227
01:23:54,960 --> 01:23:57,320
[heavy steps approaching]

1228
01:24:00,400 --> 01:24:01,520
<i>Open your eyes!</i>

1229
01:24:02,800 --> 01:24:03,920
I don't see anything!

1230
01:24:04,000 --> 01:24:05,120
Look!

1231
01:24:05,200 --> 01:24:06,200
The boot! Gimme the boot!

1232
01:24:06,280 --> 01:24:07,320
<i>Open your eyes!</i>

1233
01:24:07,400 --> 01:24:09,520
Crazy bastard, you're making me do this!

1234
01:24:52,800 --> 01:24:54,920
[cawing]

1235
01:24:55,000 --> 01:24:56,640
[plates clanging]

1236
01:24:56,720 --> 01:24:58,400
[glass smashing]

1237
01:25:02,440 --> 01:25:04,200
Hoffman, are you there?

1238
01:25:04,240 --> 01:25:07,920
- [cawing]
- [glass smashing]

1239
01:25:08,000 --> 01:25:10,800
Hoffman, are you there?

1240
01:25:10,880 --> 01:25:14,280
<i>[radio static]</i>

1241
01:25:14,320 --> 01:25:15,320
<i>[James]
Abby?</i>

1242
01:25:15,400 --> 01:25:18,280
Jim? Are you okay?

1243
01:25:18,320 --> 01:25:20,600
<i>I'm a... I'm a...</i>

1244
01:25:20,680 --> 01:25:22,680
I'm okay.

1245
01:25:24,520 --> 01:25:27,000
<i>[Abby]
Where's Pollack?</i>

1246
01:25:27,080 --> 01:25:29,960
Uh, he took off.

1247
01:25:31,480 --> 01:25:32,680
I'm alone.

1248
01:25:35,520 --> 01:25:37,680
Me, too.

1249
01:25:37,760 --> 01:25:40,520
<i>All right. Well, Just hang on.</i>

1250
01:25:40,560 --> 01:25:42,200
<i>I'm so close.</i>

1251
01:25:42,280 --> 01:25:44,480
<i>[maniacal laughing]
I'm so close.</i>

1252
01:25:46,640 --> 01:25:48,200
[chuckles, mutters]

1253
01:25:50,320 --> 01:25:52,480
<i>[radio static]</i>

1254
01:25:52,560 --> 01:25:54,160
<i>We're gonna get out of this, Jim.</i>

1255
01:25:54,240 --> 01:25:55,720
You know, daylight's coming,

1256
01:25:55,800 --> 01:25:59,200
and they're gonna
send somebody for us,

1257
01:25:59,280 --> 01:26:03,080
so we're gonna get out of this.

1258
01:26:03,120 --> 01:26:05,160
<i>You're gonna get out,</i>

1259
01:26:05,240 --> 01:26:07,680
<i>and you're gonna tell the
whole world what happened.</i>

1260
01:26:07,760 --> 01:26:09,520
You're going to sound the alarm.

1261
01:26:09,600 --> 01:26:10,960
You're going to tell the whole world.

1262
01:26:11,000 --> 01:26:13,880
And people are gonna
rise up, make change.

1263
01:26:13,960 --> 01:26:17,600
Hell, they might build you a monument.

1264
01:26:17,680 --> 01:26:19,720
Yeah.

1265
01:26:23,400 --> 01:26:25,480
The whole world's gonna
band together, Jim.

1266
01:26:33,520 --> 01:26:36,000
<i>There it is, Abby! Abby!</i>

1267
01:26:36,080 --> 01:26:37,800
<i>I can... I can see the town.</i>

1268
01:26:37,880 --> 01:26:39,560
<i>We're... We're gonna be okay.</i>

1269
01:26:39,600 --> 01:26:40,840
<i>Just hold on.</i>

1270
01:26:40,880 --> 01:26:43,000
[cawing]

1271
01:26:43,080 --> 01:26:44,000
<i>Okay.</i>

1272
01:26:50,120 --> 01:26:52,760
Jim, what's happening?

1273
01:26:52,840 --> 01:26:57,080
<i>It's Pollack. I think he's fallen.</i>

1274
01:26:57,160 --> 01:26:59,200
Is he... is he alive?

1275
01:27:01,440 --> 01:27:03,000
<i>Abby?</i>

1276
01:27:03,080 --> 01:27:06,560
Jim.

1277
01:27:06,640 --> 01:27:09,200
<i>I can't tell if this is happening.</i>

1278
01:27:09,280 --> 01:27:11,400
Jim?

1279
01:27:11,440 --> 01:27:13,400
Jim, what's happening?

1280
01:27:13,480 --> 01:27:15,520
Jim!

1281
01:27:15,600 --> 01:27:17,520
<i>[static]</i>

1282
01:27:17,600 --> 01:27:18,920
[cawing]

1283
01:27:18,960 --> 01:27:20,440
<i>[garbled dialogue, static]</i>

1284
01:27:20,520 --> 01:27:21,600
Jim!

1285
01:27:21,680 --> 01:27:23,720
- [glass smashing]
- [crows cawing]

1286
01:27:23,760 --> 01:27:26,720
<i>[garbled dialogue, static]</i>

1287
01:27:28,240 --> 01:27:30,000
[crying]

1288
01:27:30,080 --> 01:27:31,120
Jim!

1289
01:27:33,200 --> 01:27:34,520
[grunting]

1290
01:28:17,200 --> 01:28:19,440
Shoot it!

1291
01:28:19,520 --> 01:28:21,520
Town's right over there!

1292
01:28:21,600 --> 01:28:23,800
[heavy steps approaching]

1293
01:28:27,960 --> 01:28:30,760
What are you waiting for?

1294
01:28:40,080 --> 01:28:41,280
[growls]

1295
01:28:46,640 --> 01:28:50,280
[heavy breathing]

1296
01:29:02,440 --> 01:29:04,960
Mom, I'm home!

1297
01:29:10,520 --> 01:29:14,000
[Ed]
No!

1298
01:29:26,800 --> 01:29:28,720
<i>[Announcer on TV]
Let's take a look at the big picture.</i>

1299
01:29:28,800 --> 01:29:30,360
<i>We have got a lot to talk about.</i>

1300
01:29:30,440 --> 01:29:32,280
<i>Mother Nature outdoing herself right now.</i>

1301
01:29:32,360 --> 01:29:34,160
<i>Let's take a look up north.</i>

1302
01:29:34,240 --> 01:29:36,600
<i>The folks in Buffalo
are watching snow come down today.</i>

1303
01:29:36,680 --> 01:29:37,760
<i>Today they had snow,</i>

1304
01:29:37,840 --> 01:29:40,040
<i>but yesterday, a record high of 67 degrees.</i>

1305
01:29:40,080 --> 01:29:43,120
<i>So how do you deal
with those weather swings in Buffalo?</i>

1306
01:29:43,200 --> 01:29:44,520
